ch.eth.scu.importer.processor.model
Class AbstractDescriptor

java.lang.Object
  ch.eth.scu.importer.processor.model.AbstractDescriptor
Direct Known Subclasses:
BDFACSDIVAXMLProcessor.ExperimentDescriptor, BDFACSDIVAXMLProcessor.SpecimenDescriptor, BDFACSDIVAXMLProcessor.TrayDescriptor, BDFACSDIVAXMLProcessor.TubeDescriptor, BDFACSDIVAXMLProcessor.XMLFileDescriptor, LeicaLifProcessor.ImageDescriptor, LeicaLifProcessor.SubImageDescriptor, RootDescriptor
public abstract class AbstractDescriptor
extends java.lang.Object

Abstract class that represents an entity to be mapped to openBIS. Derivd classes of AbstractDescriptor will represent Experiments, Specimens, Trays (Plates), Tubes, Images, SubImages that will be wrapped into the tree viewers and will allow to map the entities to their final location in openBIS. Examples are Experiment, Specimen, Tray, Tube for the BDFACSDIVAXMLProcessor.

Author:
Aaron Ponti
